name: SectionedFetchResults.Section
desc: A collection of fetched results that share a specified identifier.

items.name: let id: SectionIdentifier
items.desc: The value that all entities in the section share for a specified key path.

items.name: var startIndex: Int
items.desc: The index of the first entity in the section.

items.name: var endIndex: Int
items.desc: The index that’s one greater than that of the last entity in the section.

items.name: subscript(Int) -> Result
items.desc: Gets the entity at the specified index within the section.

items.name: typealias Element
items.desc: A type representing the sequence’s elements.

items.name: typealias ID
items.desc: A type representing the stable identity of the entity associated with an instance.

items.name: typealias Index
items.desc: A type that represents a position in the collection.

items.name: typealias Indices
items.desc: A type that represents the indices that are valid for subscripting the collection, in ascending order.

items.name: typealias Iterator
items.desc: A type that provides the collection’s iteration interface and encapsulates its iteration state.

items.name: typealias SubSequence
items.desc: A collection representing a contiguous subrange of this collection’s elements. The subsequence shares indices with the original collection.
